.SH "NAME"
pci_get_slot \- locate PCI device for a given PCI slot
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'struct\ pci_dev\ *\ pci_get_slot('u
.BI "struct pci_dev * pci_get_slot(struct\ pci_bus\ *\ " "bus" ", unsigned\ int\ " "devfn" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIbus\fR
.RS 4
PCI bus on which desired PCI device resides
.RE
.PP
\fIdevfn\fR
.RS 4
encodes number of PCI slot in which the desired PCI device resides and the logical device number within that slot in case of multi\-function devices\&.
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Given a PCI bus and slot/function number, the desired PCI device is located in the list of PCI devices\&. If the device is found, its reference count is increased and this function returns a pointer to its data structure\&. The caller must decrement the reference count by calling
\fBpci_dev_put\fR\&. If no device is found,
\fBNULL\fR
is returned\&.
